content.description: A short stout route with a tricky crux. Originally rated .11b but perhaps a hold broke.
content.location: To the left of the main Mushroom Tip wall on a short detached area.

climbs.name: Sayonara Bitch!
climbs.fa: Equipped by Mike Snyder 2015 FA Jonathan Horst 2016

content.description: Start on a boulder leaning against the base of the wall and stretch up to a couple good crimps in a horizontal break. Make some big moves on positive holds until you reach the lip. Mantle, and immediately begin some aggro bouldering on small edges. 5th draw is hard to clip, and scary to skip. Decent clipping holds after that, but the climbing stays on you until the anchors.
content.location: In between Crazel (12d) and High Park Rodeo (13b) on the Mushroom Tip Wall. Starts off of a boulder than leans against the base of the route.

climbs.name: High Park Rodeo
climbs.fa: Est. by Mike Snyder, FA: BJ Tilden

content.description: Shared opening moves as Bo Cleevil. Cut left and pull on a tough pinch/sidepull to reach jugs. Sustained difficult movement for 4 more bolts before things begin to let up.
content.location: In the middle of the Mushroom Tip wall. Shared start with Bo Cleevil then heads left.

climbs.name: Godfather Fuzz
climbs.fa: Established by Mike Snyder, FA: BJ Tilden

content.description: Start in the obvious crack system right of Girl Next Door using handjamj, fingerlock and kneebar trickery, then move left and head straight up the blunt arete.
content.location: Find the obvious crack system on the right side of the Mushroom Tip

climbs.name: Girl Next Door
climbs.fa: Established by Mike Snyder, FA: Tyler Wilcutt

content.description: A low one move V7 boulder problem involving a small left hand crimp and a large right hand deadpoint to a finger bucket is rewarded with a fantastic shake on a massive jug with good feet.  Although you have done the hardest individual move, the route is far from over.  Find your beta through an incredibly rad redpoint crux involving an accurate move to a slot (V4/V5).  Keep it together through technical 5.12a climbing until you clip the chains! Route goes into the shade starting around Noon/1ish depending on the month!
content.location: One route right of Bo Cleevil. Start on a steep arete!

content.description: The corner / crack just left of the prominent mushroom cap. Interesting stemming, liebacking, and body english to get through it all. A little rough and new, but should clean up.
content.location: The corner / crack just left of the prominent mushroom cap in a notch with an elevated belay platform.

content.description: Climb up the corner to a ledge, continue up and left to a slaby stance. Start up trending right on a few sinker pockets thru three bolts of sequential bouldery climbing.
content.location: Start up the low obvious corner right of "Fat Boys In The Woods"

content.description: Blue streak at the end of Crag 6, furthest route left on the Mushroom Tip Wall. Climb easy terrain to enter 3 bolts of hard climbing. Obvious left stem is 'off'. Various descriptions and previous senders call this a slash grade 5.13d/5.14a or just a soft 5.14a.

Start with slightly slabby moves to a powerful undercling. Pull a fun boulder problem which could include a fun dyno to a good edge, depending on your height. Work through some 12/12- climbing for the next few bolts and get rewarded with 11ish climbing to the chains.
content.location: Middle of Mushroom tip, under a thin arch.
